...from the extreme value theorem,
as this...

32:34.578 --> 32:37.412
A simple application of the theorem...

33:01.104 --> 33:06.270
I remember how Dad once held my hand
over a lit candle.

33:08.195 --> 33:13.907
He pulled it away just before I got burned.
But it was really painful.

33:13.909 --> 33:16.196
Then he said...

33:16.870 --> 33:19.988
"Remember, this is what it's like in Hell,
all the time."

33:22.334 --> 33:24.417
Are you kidding?

33:26.922 --> 33:30.211
Are you... Aren't you angry with him?

33:30.217 --> 33:32.709
No. Or...

33:32.719 --> 33:34.551
It's a long time ago.

33:35.847 --> 33:38.305
He's actually very kind.

33:42.020 --> 33:44.512
OK!

33:44.523 --> 33:48.142
I mean it. He's really nice.

33:48.818 --> 33:50.855
I can talk about everything with him.

33:52.572 --> 33:54.529
You talk about everything with your dad?

33:54.533 --> 33:57.276
Yeah. Shouldn't I?

33:59.162 --> 34:03.076
Well, I think I've talked to my dad like...

34:03.083 --> 34:05.200
ten times.

34:05.210 --> 34:07.167
Shit.

34:10.172 --> 34:14.543
He lives abroad. Has loads of kids.

34:14.553 --> 34:16.545
Though I'm not sure he likes children.

34:20.891 --> 34:23.384
But are you angry with him?

34:29.275 --> 34:31.233
I think I was, for a while.

34:32.404 --> 34:34.360
